1. Select the VPC on your services page
2. Click on launch VPC wizard
3.  Click on create VPC. 
4. Enter the VPC name as private VPC, IPV4 CIDR block as 10.0.0.0/24
5. In IPV4 CIDR block choose amazon provided IPV6 CIDR block
6. Click on create VPC
7. Then VPC will be successfully created
8. Open the subnet option
9. Then click on create a subnet.
10. Select the created VPC.
11.   Name the subnet as per your convenience,
10 Check in the IPV6 only
11. In the IPV6 CIDR block in the second line there is space to enter a number, enter 04
12. Then click create a subnet.
13. Then go to the routing table, enter the name, add the VPC that you have created. Then click on create router table.
14.  Successfully connected four subnets to the routing table with a VPC.
15.  Go to the internet gateway, click on create internet gateway.
16. Enter the name, then click on create internet gateway.
17. Right-click on the created internet gateway, click on attach to VPC
18. Select the VPC that you have created.
19. Then click on attach internet gateway



